<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B1BFFD7FCB2F59FFB67F4B1" pageId="5" pageNumber="516" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="D126FA521B1BFFD7FCB2F59FFB69F55C" blockId="5.[806,1398,2542,2964]" pageId="5" pageNumber="516">
<emphasis id="E3ED26401B1BFFD7FCB2F59FFC51F5D7" bold="true" box="[806,961,2542,2571]" pageId="5" pageNumber="516">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B1BFFD7FC44F59FFAE0F5D7" authority="Wagner, 1848" authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1848" box="[976,1392,2542,2571]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="516" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="opimus">Ctenomys opimus Wagner, 1848</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="61F1F00F1B1BFFD7FCB3F660FB69F55C" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798388321" pageId="5" pageNumber="516">“Bolivia.” Restricted by O. Thomas in 1900 to “Sahama,” Mont Sahama, Oruro, about 17°49’ S, 67°28” W, 3000-4000 m.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D126FA521B1BFFD7FCBDF6FDFB67F4B1" blockId="5.[806,1398,2542,2964]" pageId="5" pageNumber="516">
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B1BFFD7FCBDF6FDFB98F575" authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1848" box="[809,1032,2700,2729]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="5" pageNumber="516" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="opimus">Ctenomys opimus</taxonomicName>
was initially included in Chaco group, but according to mtDNA analysis, it belongs to the opimusspecies group. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 26 and FN = 48, and sperm is symmetric. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B1BFFD7FCB2F702FB62F384" pageId="5" pageNumber="516" type="synonymic_list">
